# LESSON 3 requests. Server: npm run lesson3  (or lesson3:scaffold)
#
# This lesson is about the browser doing the fetching, so there is only one
# request. Sending it here shows the exact JSON the React page receives, which
# is useful before writing any component code.

@host = http://localhost:3300


### The endpoint the component calls
# Already working in both versions. Nothing to build on the server side.

GET {{host}}/get-all-animals
